<subSubSection id="5CF5BB355C27A2E29FF587D625317829" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2AF5F33FEBBFC1FB315D8E6DADC1EE09" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E31E8C3D91A5A38C6835FF5E0F71BDE" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
The specific name is from the Latin word 
<normalizedToken id="CD86C7EB21ECC500B284F804AC526CA8" originalValue="“curvus”">&quot;curvus&quot;</normalizedToken>
, in reference to the shape of the palpal uncus; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="45C59361F1344623FAC5111D4843207B" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B940923EB124315309518323703F9C5E" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB2AA3DAB752173CAADC43D95DAFA24C" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
